    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="1120"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1120">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/8–1054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DCD1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dillon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-10T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 10, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>576. Eyes only Secretary. At my direction, <persName>Joyce</persName> saw
                        <persName>Margerie</persName> today and conveyed to him substance of first
                    two paragraphs of <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 501.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1120fn1">Dated Aug. 9, <ref target="#pg_1928">p. 1928</ref>.</note>
                    He also told <persName>Margerie</persName> that he felt it was obvious that
                    there had been a complete misunderstanding by <persName corresp="#p_BG1"
                        >Bidault</persName>, possibly based on language difficulties.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Margerie</persName> said that he fully agreed that there must have
                    been such a misunderstanding. He added that he remembered April 23 very well
                    because on that day <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> had been ill,
                    jittery, overwrought, and at his very worst. <persName>Margerie</persName> added
                    that on that day <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> had been
                    “incoherent” to members of his own top staff. Therefore, he very readily
                    understood how such a misunderstanding could have come about on that particular
                    day.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName>Margerie</persName> said that he was very grateful that this subject
                    had been cleared up and hoped that knowledge of this misunderstanding would be
                    kept strictly limited. He said that he would undertake to see <persName
                        corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> personally and straighten him out on
                    this subject.</p>
                <p>I remember <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>’s condition on that day
                    very well myself and I am sure that it is the complete explanation for his
                    otherwise incomprehensible misunderstanding.</p>
                <p>I hope to be able to show statement to <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        >Schumann</persName> tomorrow. I will emphasize to him that this is being
                    done merely as a courtesy.</p>
                <p>In view of tense parliamentary situation here, I thoroughly agree <pb facs="0552"
                        n="1934" xml:id="pg_1934"/> with <persName>Parodi</persName> and
                        <persName>Margerie</persName> that publication of statement should be
                    postponed until after <gloss target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss> debate.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d1120fn2">Regarding the disposition of the question of the
                        statement, see memorandum by Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                            >Dulles</persName> to the President, Aug. 24, <ref target="#pg_1976">p.
                            1976</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dillon</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
